ssName.name: ssName
ssName.description: The StreetTalk name of the server, up to 15 characters long.

ssNetid.name: ssNetid
ssNetid.description: The VINES network ID of the server, which is equal to the server's serial number. This ID may be up to 4 bytes in length.

ssSwRev.name: ssSwRev
ssSwRev.description: The VINES software revision for this server.

ssLoadAvg1.name: ssLoadAvg1
ssLoadAvg1.description: The one minute exponential decaying average of server load.

ssLoadAvg5.name: ssLoadAvg5
ssLoadAvg5.description: The five minute exponential decaying average of server load.

ssLoadAvg15.name: ssLoadAvg15
ssLoadAvg15.description: The 15 minute exponential decaying average of server load.

ssMsgAvg1.name: ssMsgAvg1
ssMsgAvg1.description: The one minute exponential decaying average of network messages sent and received per second.

ssMsgsIn.name: ssMsgsIn
ssMsgsIn.description: The total number of network messages that the server has received over the network since the last reboot.

ssMsgsOut.name: ssMsgsOut
ssMsgsOut.description: The total number of network messages that the server has sent over the network since the last reboot.

ssDrops.name: ssDrops
ssDrops.description: The total number of received messages that could not be processed due to a lack of communications buffer space.

ssSwapAvg.name: ssSwapAvg
ssSwapAvg.description: An exponential decaying average of the number of times a process was swapped to or from disk per second over a one minute period.

ssProdDescr.name: ssProdDescr
ssProdDescr.description: The description of the product type.

ssRealMemory.name: ssRealMemory
ssRealMemory.description: The total amount of RAM, in kilobytes, configured in the server.

ssOsType.name: ssOsType
ssOsType.description: The type of server OS. UNIX is the only operating system supported.

ssSystemUptime.name: ssSystemUptime
ssSystemUptime.description: The amount time since this host was last initialized. Note that this is different from sysUpTime because sysUpTime is the uptime of the network management portion of the system.

ssSystemDate.name: ssSystemDate
ssSystemDate.description: The current time on the server.

ssSystemStatus.name: ssSystemStatus
ssSystemStatus.description: The status of the server. When the server is initialized this field will get set to running. When a shutdown is requested the server will shutdown all services and await a manual reboot. A reboot request will shut down all services and automatically reboot the machine.

ssUserLicenseCfg.name: ssUserLicenseCfg
ssUserLicenseCfg.description: The user limit license for this server.

svcNumber.name: svcNumber
svcNumber.description: The number of services in the svcTable.

svcTable.name: svcTable
svcTable.description: A list of services on the server.

svcEntry.name: svcEntry
svcEntry.description: Each entry contains a set of statistics for one service.

svcIndex.name: svcIndex
svcIndex.description: A unique value for each service used by SNMP to keep track of service table entries. This value may vary if the table changes.

svcName.name: svcName
svcName.description: The StreetTalk name of the service, the names are of the form 'item@group@organization'.

svcStatus.name: svcStatus
svcStatus.description: The status of the service. Running - available to users. Initializing - starting and will be available shortly. Crashing - not functioning properly. Inconsistent - the name cannot be found. Stopped - not running. Only running and stopped are valid for sets.

svcUpTime.name: svcUpTime
svcUpTime.description: The amount of time that the service has been running.

svcMsgsIn.name: svcMsgsIn
svcMsgsIn.description: The total number of messages that the service has received over the network since the service was last started.

svcMsgsOut.name: svcMsgsOut
svcMsgsOut.description: The total number of messages that the service has sent over the network since the service was last started.

svcLocIn.name: svcLocIn
svcLocIn.description: The number of messages received by the service that were sent by entities that are local to the service's server since the service was last started.

svcLocOut.name: svcLocOut
svcLocOut.description: The number of messages sent by the service to entities that are local to the service's server since the service was last started.

svcActSess.name: svcActSess
svcActSess.description: The number of active sessions with the service.

svcTotSess.name: svcTotSess
svcTotSess.description: The total number of sessions that the service has handled since it was last started.

svcCategory.name: svcCategory
svcCategory.description: The type of service defined as follows: 1 Server Service 2 File Service or DOS/UNIX bridge file service 3 Print Service 4 Mail Service 5 StreetTalk Service 6 Time 7 File Transfer Protocol (FTP) 8 Semaphore Service 9 System Network Architecture Service 10 Virtual Terminal Service 11 Asynchronous Terminal Service 12 Netbios Service 13 PC-Based Service 14 Bisynchronous Service 15 APPC Service(APPCCAT) 16 Network Management Service 17 VINES Security Service 18 StreetTalk Directory Assistance Service 19 AppleTalk Filing Protocol (AFP) 20 VINES Configuration Service 21 Event Management Service 22 Link Service 23 Backup Service 24 Unused 25 VINES Remote Service 26 Remote Execution Service 27 Tree Service 28 VINES Proxy Agent Service 29 WAN Configuration Service 30 AppleTalk Agent Service 31 Alert Management Service 32 Unused 33 Unused 34 Unused 35 Remote Program Load Service 36 StreetTalk Agent Service 37 NetWare Print Queue Service 38 NetWare Print Service 39 NetWare File Service 100 AdminList 1986 VINES Assistant Service 1888 SMTP Service Third-party services return values from 1000 to 1899.

svcCpuTime.name: svcCpuTime
svcCpuTime.description: The amount of current CPU use that the service is generating.

svcSize.name: svcSize
svcSize.description: The amount of virtual memory that is allocated to the service.

svcSockets.name: svcSockets
svcSockets.description: The number of VINES sockets that the service is currently consuming.

svcSPPs.name: svcSPPs
svcSPPs.description: The number of SPP connections that the service is currently consuming.

svcLogMask.name: svcLogMask
svcLogMask.description: The current log mask of a service.

svcUserTable.name: svcUserTable
svcUserTable.description: A list of the users for the services.

svcUserEntry.name: svcUserEntry
svcUserEntry.description: An entry in the list of service users.

svcUserSvcIndex.name: svcUserSvcIndex
svcUserSvcIndex.description: A unique value for each service on the server, used by SNMP to order the list.

svcUserIndex.name: svcUserIndex
svcUserIndex.description: A unique value for each user of a service. This value will change as new users are added and old users deleted from the service.

svcUserSvcName.name: svcUserSvcName
svcUserSvcName.description: The StreetTalk name of the service.

svcUserName.name: svcUserName
svcUserName.description: The StreetTalk name of the user of the service.

dskNumber.name: dskNumber
dskNumber.description: The number of disks in the disk table.

dskTable.name: dskTable
dskTable.description: A list of statistics for the disks on this server.

dskIndex.name: dskIndex
dskIndex.description: A unique value for each disk on the server, used by SNMP to order the table.

dskName.name: dskName
dskName.description: The name of the disk unit.

dskUtil.name: dskUtil
dskUtil.description: A five minute exponential decaying average showing the percentage of time that the disk unit was in use transferring data.

dskDemand.name: dskDemand
dskDemand.description: A five minute exponential decaying average showing the percentage of time that the disk unit needed to be used to satisfy all requests.

dskSizeMB.name: dskSizeMB
dskSizeMB.description: The size of the disk in megabytes.

dskUsedPct.name: dskUsedPct
dskUsedPct.description: The percentage of disk space that is currently in use.

dskStatus.name: dskStatus
dskStatus.description: The disks status, 1 is non-operational, 2 is operational.

dskNOperations.name: dskNOperations
dskNOperations.description: The total number of reads and writes for the disk since the server was last booted.

dskNBlocks.name: dskNBlocks
dskNBlocks.description: The total number of 1-kilobyte data blocks transferred to and from the disk since the server was last booted.

dskResp.name: dskResp
dskResp.description: The total amount of time processes spent waiting for a response from the disks.

dskActive.name: dskActive
dskActive.description: The total amount of the disk was active.

dskNMisc.name: dskNMisc
dskNMisc.description: The total number of miscellaneous disk operations since the server was last booted.

dskNErrs.name: dskNErrs
dskNErrs.description: The total number of disk errors that were not logged since the server was last booted.

dskPctBusy.name: dskPctBusy
dskPctBusy.description: A five minute exponential decaying average showing the percentage of time that the disk spent servicing data transfer requests.

dskAvgWait.name: dskAvgWait
dskAvgWait.description: A five minute exponential decaying average showing the average amount of time that read and write requests waited on the request queue to be serviced.

dskAvgService.name: dskAvgService
dskAvgService.description: A five minute exponential decaying average showing the average amount of time that the disk took to service read and write requests.

fsTotCache.name: fsTotCache
fsTotCache.description: The amount of server RAM, in kilobytes, that is used for caching purposes. This is configurable from the server's console. Note: The setting of this object will not take effect until the server is rebooted.

fsCacheBufSize.name: fsCacheBufSize
fsCacheBufSize.description: The amount of server RAM, in kilobytes, that makes up a file system cache buffer. Also configurable from the console. Note: The setting of this object will not take effect until the server is rebooted.

fsMaxOpenFiles.name: fsMaxOpenFiles
fsMaxOpenFiles.description: The largest number of open files on the server at a single point in time.

fsOpenFiles.name: fsOpenFiles
fsOpenFiles.description: The number of files currently open.

fsMaxOpensOnFiles.name: fsMaxOpensOnFiles
fsMaxOpensOnFiles.description: The largest number of open operations on files at a single point in time. There can be more than one open operation on an open file. For example, two users may open the same file. This file would count as one open file and two open operations on the file.

fsOpensOnFiles.name: fsOpensOnFiles
fsOpensOnFiles.description: The current number of open operations on files.

fsRecLocks.name: fsRecLocks
fsRecLocks.description: The current number of record locks.

fsMaxRecLocks.name: fsMaxRecLocks
fsMaxRecLocks.description: The largest number of simultaneous record locks.

fsPctCacheHits.name: fsPctCacheHits
fsPctCacheHits.description: The percentage of cache buffer requests that the system was able to service using existing cache buffers, without reading new data from disk.

fsCacheUnavail.name: fsCacheUnavail
fsCacheUnavail.description: The number of cache buffer requests that the server was unable to service without reading new data from disk.

commTotBufs.name: commTotBufs
commTotBufs.description: The total communications buffer space (the amount of server RAM used for network communications) in kilobytes. This is configurable from the server's console. Note: The setting of this object will not take effect until the servers is rebooted.

commBufUsage.name: commBufUsage
commBufUsage.description: The percentage of the communications buffer space currently in use.

commAllocsFailed.name: commAllocsFailed
commAllocsFailed.description: The cumulative total of the number of buffers that could not be allocated since the server was last booted.

commSocksCfg.name: commSocksCfg
commSocksCfg.description: The maximum number of sockets that can be open at one time. Configurable from the server console. Note: The setting of this object will not take effect until the servers is rebooted.

commSocksInUse.name: commSocksInUse
commSocksInUse.description: The percentage of the maximum configured sockets in use.

commMaxOpenSocks.name: commMaxOpenSocks
commMaxOpenSocks.description: The maximum number of sockets in use since the server was last booted.

vipTotIn.name: vipTotIn
vipTotIn.description: The total number of VINES IP packets that the server has received since the server was last booted.

vipTotOut.name: vipTotOut
vipTotOut.description: The total number of VINES IP packets that the server has sent since the server was last booted.

vipBad.name: vipBad
vipBad.description: The number of packets that the server has received since the server was last booted that had an incorrect checksum.

vipRouted.name: vipRouted
vipRouted.description: The total number of packets that were routed to another node since the server was last booted.

vipRoutedHWM.name: vipRoutedHWM
vipRoutedHWM.description: The largest number of packets routed in 1 second since the server was last booted.

vipBcast.name: vipBcast
vipBcast.description: The number of VINES IP broadcast packets sent, both generated from the server and routed from other nodes.

vipBcastHWM.name: vipBcastHWM
vipBcastHWM.description: The largest number of packets broadcast in 1 second since the server was last booted.

vipReass.name: vipReass
vipReass.description: The number of times packets were reassembled since the server was last booted. One VINES IP packet being broken into three message fragments is counted as one fragmentation. The three fragments being reassembled into one VINES IP packet counts as one reassembly.

vipFrags.name: vipFrags
vipFrags.description: The number of packet fragmentations performed since the server was last booted.

vipToDodIP.name: vipToDodIP
vipToDodIP.description: The number of packets that VINES IP passed to DARPA IP (TCP/IP) for encapsulation in IP headers since the server was last booted.

vipFromDodIP.name: vipFromDodIP
vipFromDodIP.description: The number of packets that VINES IP received from DARPA IP (TCP/IP) since the server was last booted.

vipInFragments.name: vipInFragments
vipInFragments.description: The number of fragments received since the server was last booted.

vipTooSmall.name: vipTooSmall
vipTooSmall.description: The number of packets that the server has received since the server was last booted that were too small.

vipBadLength.name: vipBadLength
vipBadLength.description: The number of packets that the server has received since the server was last booted that had an invalid packet length in the packet length field of the VINES IP header.

vipNoBuffers.name: vipNoBuffers
vipNoBuffers.description: The number of packets that the server could not send, receive or route due to a lack of communication buffers since the server was last booted.

vrtpNbrNumber.name: vrtpNbrNumber
vrtpNbrNumber.description: The number of entries in the neighbor table (NbrTable).

vrtpNbrTable.name: vrtpNbrTable
vrtpNbrTable.description: A list of information about neighbors of this server.

vrtpNbrEntry.name: vrtpNbrEntry
vrtpNbrEntry.description: The information for each entry in the table.

vrtpNbrNetid.name: vrtpNbrNetid
vrtpNbrNetid.description: The network ID of the neighbor, which is the first part of the neighbor's VINES internet address. If the neighbor is a server the network number is the server's serial number.

vrtpNbrSubNetid.name: vrtpNbrSubNetid
vrtpNbrSubNetid.description: The subnetwork ID of the neighbor, which is the second part of the neighbor's VINES internet address. If the neighbor is a server the subnetwork number is 1.

vrtpNbrType.name: vrtpNbrType
vrtpNbrType.description: The type of the neighbor (workstation = pc).

vrtpNbrIfType.name: vrtpNbrIfType
vrtpNbrIfType.description: The type of interface that the server uses to reach the neighbor.

vrtpNbrRemAddress.name: vrtpNbrRemAddress
vrtpNbrRemAddress.description: The address of the neighbor's physical interface, such as a LAN address. If the neighbor is connected via an HDLC or asynchronous line this object specifies an internal ID.

vrtpNbrLocAddress.name: vrtpNbrLocAddress
vrtpNbrLocAddress.description: The address of the server's physical interface, such as a LAN address.

vrtpNbrLocSlot.name: vrtpNbrLocSlot
vrtpNbrLocSlot.description: The slot number of the interface card that the server uses to reach the neighbor.

vrtpNbrLocLine.name: vrtpNbrLocLine
vrtpNbrLocLine.description: The number of the line on the serial card that the server uses to reach the neighbor. It does not apply to neighbors that are reached over LANs.

vrtpNbrSvrName.name: vrtpNbrSvrName
vrtpNbrSvrName.description: The name of the neighbor. If the neighbor is a workstation then this object has no meaning.

vrtpRtNumber.name: vrtpRtNumber
vrtpRtNumber.description: The number of entires in the route table (RtTable).

vrtpRtTable.name: vrtpRtTable
vrtpRtTable.description: A list of networks and the routing information to find them.

vrtpRtNetid.name: vrtpRtNetid
vrtpRtNetid.description: The network ID of the route's destination server.

vrtpRtMetric.name: vrtpRtMetric
vrtpRtMetric.description: The routing metric used by the called server to reach the destination. The metric reflects the cost of the path to the destination, it is in 200-millisecond units.

vrtpRtIdle.name: vrtpRtIdle
vrtpRtIdle.description: The time to live timer for this route's entry. This value indicicates the amount of time before the entry is removed from the called server's routing table. The value is returned in 90 second units.

vrtpRtGateNetid.name: vrtpRtGateNetid
vrtpRtGateNetid.description: The network ID of the server that acts as the router for reaching the destination server.

vrtpRtSvrName.name: vrtpRtSvrName
vrtpRtSvrName.description: The name of the destination server.

vrtpRtGateSvrName.name: vrtpRtGateSvrName
vrtpRtGateSvrName.description: The name of the server that acts as the router for reaching the destination server.

vrtpTotIn.name: vrtpTotIn
vrtpTotIn.description: The number of VINES VRTP packets received since the server was last booted.

vrtpTotOut.name: vrtpTotOut
vrtpTotOut.description: The number of VINES VRTP packets sent since the server was last booted.

vrtpErrsIn.name: vrtpErrsIn
vrtpErrsIn.description: The number of errors the VRTP protocol encountered while receiving packets, since the server was last booted.

vrtpNoBuffersIn.name: vrtpNoBuffersIn
vrtpNoBuffersIn.description: The number of times that no communication buffers were available to process received RTP packets or create routine table entries.

vrtpUpdatesIn.name: vrtpUpdatesIn
vrtpUpdatesIn.description: The total number of update packets received.

vrtpRqstLkUpIn.name: vrtpRqstLkUpIn
vrtpRqstLkUpIn.description: The number of packets received that requested routing information.

vrtpRqstSlrInfoIn.name: vrtpRqstSlrInfoIn
vrtpRqstSlrInfoIn.description: The number of request packets received that requested VINES routine metric information on a source-level route (Sequenced Only).

vrtpReinitIn.name: vrtpReinitIn
vrtpReinitIn.description: The number reinitialization packets received (Sequenced Only).

vrtpResyncIn.name: vrtpResyncIn
vrtpResyncIn.description: The number of resynchronization operations or update packets received that contained information for synchronizing routing table entries.

vrtpRedirIn.name: vrtpRedirIn
vrtpRedirIn.description: The number of redirect packets received.

vrtpFragsIn.name: vrtpFragsIn
vrtpFragsIn.description: The number of update or response fragments received (Sequenced Only).

vrtpFragsDropIn.name: vrtpFragsDropIn
vrtpFragsDropIn.description: The number of packets dropped due to either the time taken to reassemble was too long or no communication buffer were available(SEQUENCED ONLY).

vrtpFragsBadIn.name: vrtpFragsBadIn
vrtpFragsBadIn.description: The number of RTP fragments discarded because they had packet IDs that were out-of-sequence (SEQUENCED ONLY).

vrtpFragsDupIn.name: vrtpFragsDupIn
vrtpFragsDupIn.description: The number of RTP fragments that were dropped because they were duplicates of other fragments (SEQUENCED ONLY).

vrtpFragsDoneIn.name: vrtpFragsDoneIn
vrtpFragsDoneIn.description: The number of updates and responses that were fragmented or reassembled successfully(SEQUENCED ONLY).

vrtpReassBadIn.name: vrtpReassBadIn
vrtpReassBadIn.description: The number of updates and responses that were not successfully fragmented or reassembled (SEQUENCED ONLY).

vrtpOutdatedIn.name: vrtpOutdatedIn
vrtpOutdatedIn.description: The number of received RTP packets discarded because they were outdated (SEQUENCED ONLY).

vrtpNetInfoBad.name: vrtpNetInfoBad
vrtpNetInfoBad.description: The number of received outdated entries for logical networks (SEQUENCED ONLY).

vrtpBadRdrs.name: vrtpBadRdrs
vrtpBadRdrs.description: The number of redirect packets discarded because of a bad length.

vrtpBdcstIn.name: vrtpBdcstIn
vrtpBdcstIn.description: The number of broadcasted RTP update packets received.

vrtpNoBuffersOut.name: vrtpNoBuffersOut
vrtpNoBuffersOut.description: The number of times that no communication buffers were available to send RTP packets.

vrtpUpdatesOut.name: vrtpUpdatesOut
vrtpUpdatesOut.description: The total number of update packets sent.

vrtpRqstLkUpOut.name: vrtpRqstLkUpOut
vrtpRqstLkUpOut.description: The number of packets sent that requested routing information.

vrtpRqstSlrInfoOut.name: vrtpRqstSlrInfoOut
vrtpRqstSlrInfoOut.description: The number of request packets sent that requested VINES routine metric information on a source-level route (SEQUENCED ONLY).

vrtpReinitOut.name: vrtpReinitOut
vrtpReinitOut.description: The number reinitialization packets sent (SEQUENCED ONLY).

vrtpResyncOut.name: vrtpResyncOut
vrtpResyncOut.description: The number of resynchronization operations or update packets sent that contained information for synchronizing routing table entries.

vrtpRedirOut.name: vrtpRedirOut
vrtpRedirOut.description: The number of redirect packets sent.

vrtpFragsOut.name: vrtpFragsOut
vrtpFragsOut.description: The number of update or response fragments sent (SEQUENCED ONLY).

vrtpFragsDoneOut.name: vrtpFragsDoneOut
vrtpFragsDoneOut.description: The number of updates and responses that were fragmented successfully (SEQUENCED ONLY).

vrtpFragsBadOut.name: vrtpFragsBadOut
vrtpFragsBadOut.description: The number of updates and responses that were fragmented unsuccessfully (SEQUENCED ONLY).

vrtpFragsDropOut.name: vrtpFragsDropOut
vrtpFragsDropOut.description: The number of packets dropped due to either the time taken to fragment the message was too long or no communication buffer were available (SEQUENCED ONLY).

vrtpBdcstOut.name: vrtpBdcstOut
vrtpBdcstOut.description: The number of broadcasted RTP update packets sent.

vrtpRtCr.name: vrtpRtCr
vrtpRtCr.description: The number of routes created by redirect packets.

vrtpRtMod.name: vrtpRtMod
vrtpRtMod.description: The number of routes modified by redirect packets.

vrtpNbrAnchors.name: vrtpNbrAnchors
vrtpNbrAnchors.description: The total entries in the neighbor table or total paths to all neighbors.

vrtpNbrEntries.name: vrtpNbrEntries
vrtpNbrEntries.description: The total entries in the neighbor table or total paths to all neighbors.

vrtpNetEntries.name: vrtpNetEntries
vrtpNetEntries.description: The total entries for networks in this server's network table.

vrtpLkUp.name: vrtpLkUp
vrtpLkUp.description: The number of calls to look up network table entries by the server.

vrtpBadLkUp.name: vrtpBadLkUp
vrtpBadLkUp.description: The number of calls to look up network table entries by the server that failed.

vrtpNonSeqTotIn.name: vrtpNonSeqTotIn
vrtpNonSeqTotIn.description: The number of non-sequenced RTP packets received.

vrtpNonSeqTotOut.name: vrtpNonSeqTotOut
vrtpNonSeqTotOut.description: The number of non-sequenced RTP packets sent.

vrtpNonSeqErrsIn.name: vrtpNonSeqErrsIn
vrtpNonSeqErrsIn.description: The number of errors while receiving non-sequenced RTP packets.

vrtpNonSeqUpdIn.name: vrtpNonSeqUpdIn
vrtpNonSeqUpdIn.description: The number of non-sequenced update packets received.

vrtpNonSeqRspIn.name: vrtpNonSeqRspIn
vrtpNonSeqRspIn.description: The number of non-sequenced responses received.

vrtpNonSeqRqstIn.name: vrtpNonSeqRqstIn
vrtpNonSeqRqstIn.description: The number of non-sequenced requests received.

vrtpNonSeqRdrIn.name: vrtpNonSeqRdrIn
vrtpNonSeqRdrIn.description: The number of non-sequenced redirect packets received.

vrtpBadNonSeqRdrIn.name: vrtpBadNonSeqRdrIn
vrtpBadNonSeqRdrIn.description: The number of invalid non-sequenced redirect packets received.

vrtpNonSeqBdcstIn.name: vrtpNonSeqBdcstIn
vrtpNonSeqBdcstIn.description: The number of non-sequenced broadcast packets received.

vrtpNonSeqUpdOut.name: vrtpNonSeqUpdOut
vrtpNonSeqUpdOut.description: The number of non-sequenced update packets sent.

vrtpNonSeqRspOut.name: vrtpNonSeqRspOut
vrtpNonSeqRspOut.description: The number of non-sequenced responses sent.

vrtpNonSeqRqstOut.name: vrtpNonSeqRqstOut
vrtpNonSeqRqstOut.description: The number of non-sequenced requests sent.

vrtpNonSeqRdrOut.name: vrtpNonSeqRdrOut
vrtpNonSeqRdrOut.description: The number of non-sequenced redirect packets sent.

vrtpNonSeqBdcstOut.name: vrtpNonSeqBdcstOut
vrtpNonSeqBdcstOut.description: The number of non-sequenced broadcast packets sent.

vsppConnsInUse.name: vsppConnsInUse
vsppConnsInUse.description: The number of SPP connections currently in use by processes on the server.

vsppConnsCfg.name: vsppConnsCfg
vsppConnsCfg.description: The allowable maximum number of SPP connections that can be in use by processes on the server at one time. Note: The setting of this object will not take effect until the servers is rebooted.

vsppMaxConns.name: vsppMaxConns
vsppMaxConns.description: The maximum number of SPP connections in use at a single point in time since the server was last booted.

vsppTotIn.name: vsppTotIn
vsppTotIn.description: The total number of VINES SPP packets that the server has received since the server was last booted.

vsppTotOut.name: vsppTotOut
vsppTotOut.description: The total number of VINES SPP packets that the server has sent since the server was last booted.

vsppInErrs.name: vsppInErrs
vsppInErrs.description: The number of SPP errors encountered while receiving packets, since the server was last booted.

vsppBadType.name: vsppBadType
vsppBadType.description: The total number of packets received on SPP connections that had invalid SPP packet types.

vsppNoBuffers.name: vsppNoBuffers
vsppNoBuffers.description: The number of packets that the server could not send, receive or route due to a lack of communication buffers since the server was last booted.

vsppNoPort.name: vsppNoPort
vsppNoPort.description: The number of incoming packets that the server dropped due to an unmatched destination port or an unmatched connection ID.

vsppDups.name: vsppDups
vsppDups.description: The number of incoming packets that were duplicates of other packets.

vsppBadOrder.name: vsppBadOrder
vsppBadOrder.description: The number of incoming packets that were received out of order.

vsppDataIn.name: vsppDataIn
vsppDataIn.description: The number of packets received on SPP connections.

vsppAcksIn.name: vsppAcksIn
vsppAcksIn.description: The number of acknowledgement packets received.

vsppDiscIn.name: vsppDiscIn
vsppDiscIn.description: The number of disconnected packets received on SPP connections.

vsppProbesIn.name: vsppProbesIn
vsppProbesIn.description: The number of probe packets received on SPP connections.

vsppDataOut.name: vsppDataOut

vifLnkType.description: The type of data link level protocol used on this line. 1 Asynchronous Terminal Emulation. 7 Block asynchronous. 8 High-level Data Link Control (HDLC). 9 X.25 10 Synchronous DataLink Control (SDLC) 1. 11 3270/BSC bisynchronous communication. 12 Same as SDLC1 except line is connected to an ICA card.

vifLnkDrops.name: vifLnkDrops

vifLnkUnders.name: vifLnkUnders

vifLnkOvers.name: vifLnkOvers
vifLnkOvers.description: The total number of receiver overrun errors on receive.

vifLnkFrmErrs.name: vifLnkFrmErrs
vifLnkFrmErrs.description: The total number of framing errors.

vifX25VCNumber.name: vifX25VCNumber

vifX25VCTable.description: A list of X.25 packet level statistics for the virtual circuit.

vifX25VCSession.name: vifX25VCSession

vifX25VCBytesAwaitAck.description: The total number of bytes transmitted that are awaiting acknowledgement.

vifX25VCPktsIn.name: vifX25VCPktsIn
vifX25VCPktsIn.description: The total number of X.25 packets that have been received.

vifX25VCBytesIn.name: vifX25VCBytesIn
vifX25VCBytesIn.description: The total number of bytes received.

vifX25VCResetsIn.name: vifX25VCResetsIn
vifX25VCResetsIn.description: The total number of X.25 reset packets received.

vifX25VCResetsOut.name: vifX25VCResetsOut
vifX25VCResetsOut.description: The total number of X.25 reset packets transmitted.

vifX25VCLogChnNum.name: vifX25VCLogChnNum
vifX25VCLogChnNum.description: The logical channel number of the X.25 VC.

vifX25VCRemAddr.name: vifX25VCRemAddr

vifStatIndex.description: A unique value for each statistic, used by SNMP to order the table.

vifStatDescr.name: vifStatDescr
vifStatDescr.description: A brief description of the statistic.

oscpuEntry.name: oscpuEntry
oscpuEntry.description: Each entry contains a set of statistics for one CPU.

cpuIndex.name: cpuIndex
cpuIndex.description: A unique value for each processor on the server.

cpuUserUsage.name: cpuUserUsage
cpuUserUsage.description: The amount of time the CPU spent running processes that run in user space since boot time.

cpuSysUsage.name: cpuSysUsage
cpuSysUsage.description: The amount of time the CPU spent running processes that run in system mode since boottime.

cpuWIOUserUsage.name: cpuWIOUserUsage
cpuWIOUserUsage.description: The amount of time that the CPU was idle, but at least one process was waiting for an I/O operation to complete, since boot time.

cpuProcSwappedOut.name: cpuProcSwappedOut
cpuProcSwappedOut.description: The amount of time that the CPU had processes swapped out.

cpuWIOUsage.name: cpuWIOUsage
cpuWIOUsage.description: The amout of time that the CPU waited for I/O to occur.

cpuWSUsage.name: cpuWSUsage
cpuWSUsage.description: The amout of time that the CPU waited for a swap to occur.

cpuWPIOUsage.name: cpuWPIOUsage
cpuWPIOUsage.description: The amout of time that the CPU waited for device I/O to occur.

osBReads.name: osBReads
osBReads.description: The number of transfers from disk to system buffers since boot time.

osBWrites.name: osBWrites
osBWrites.description: The number of transfers from system buffers to disk since boot time.

osLReads.name: osLReads
osLReads.description: The number of reads on the system buffers since boot time.

osLWrites.name: osLWrites
osLWrites.description: The number of writes on the system buffers since boot time.

osPReads.name: osPReads
osPReads.description: The number of reads via the raw (physical) device mechanism since boot time.

osPWrites.name: osPWrites
osPWrites.description: The number of writes via the raw (physical) device mechanism since boot time.

osInSwaps.name: osInSwaps
osInSwaps.description: The number of swaps in since boot time.

osOutSwaps.name: osOutSwaps
osOutSwaps.description: The number of swaps out since boot time.

osInBSwaps.name: osInBSwaps
osInBSwaps.description: The number of 4 KB buffers transferred in since boot time.

osOutBSwaps.name: osOutBSwaps
osOutBSwaps.description: The number of 4 KB buffers transferred out since boot time.

osProcessSwitches.name: osProcessSwitches
osProcessSwitches.description: The number of process switches since boot time.

osSystemCalls.name: osSystemCalls
osSystemCalls.description: The number of system calls since boot time.

osSystemRead.name: osSystemRead
osSystemRead.description: The number of system read calls.

osSystemWrite.name: osSystemWrite
osSystemWrite.description: The number of system write calls.

osSystemFork.name: osSystemFork
osSystemFork.description: The number of system fork calls.

osSystemExec.name: osSystemExec
osSystemExec.description: The number of system exec calls.

osRunQueue.name: osRunQueue
osRunQueue.description: The number of processes on the run queue.

osRunQueueOcc.name: osRunQueueOcc
osRunQueueOcc.description: The amount of time that processes were on the run queue.

osSwapQueueTotals.name: osSwapQueueTotals
osSwapQueueTotals.description: The number of processes on the swap queue.

osSwapQueueOcc.name: osSwapQueueOcc
osSwapQueueOcc.description: The amount of time that processes were on the swap queue.

osIPCMsgOps.name: osIPCMsgOps
osIPCMsgOps.description: The number of times a System V IPC message operation occurred.

osSemOps.name: osSemOps
osSemOps.description: The number of semaphore operations performed by processes.

osPnpFault.name: osPnpFault
osPnpFault.description: The number of times a process accessed a page which had not been page faulted in.

osWrtFault.name: osWrtFault
osWrtFault.description: The number of times processes attempted to write to a page marked as copy-on-write.

osCurrentInodes.name: osCurrentInodes
osCurrentInodes.description: The number of inode table entries currently in the inode table.

osHWInodes.name: osHWInodes
osHWInodes.description: The high water mark of inode table entries in use since the last reboot of the called server.

osCurrentFiles.name: osCurrentFiles
osCurrentFiles.description: The number of open file table entries currently in the open file table.

osHWFiles.name: osHWFiles
osHWFiles.description: The high water mark of open file table entries in use since the last reboot of the called server.

osMaxInodes.name: osMaxInodes
osMaxInodes.description: The maximum number of inode table entries in the inode table.

osMaxFiles.name: osMaxFiles
osMaxFiles.description: The maximum number of open file table entries in the open file table.

osMaxProcesses.name: osMaxProcesses
osMaxProcesses.description: The maximum number of process table entries that UNIX on the server allocates.

osSwapSpaceAvailable.name: osSwapSpaceAvailable
osSwapSpaceAvailable.description: The amount of swap space available in 512 byte blocks.

osFreeMemoryTotal.name: osFreeMemoryTotal
osFreeMemoryTotal.description: The total amount of executable space in kilobytes.

osIOBufs.name: osIOBufs
osIOBufs.description: The number of 1 KB system buffers that make up UNIX cache on the server.

osMounts.name: osMounts
osMounts.description: The number of mount table entries that UNIX on the server allocates.

osUserMaxPu.name: osUserMaxPu
osUserMaxPu.description: The maximum number of concurrent UNIX processes that can be run by users other than the superuser.

osUserMaxFp.name: osUserMaxFp
osUserMaxFp.description: The maximum number of open files per process.

osCurrentProcesses.name: osCurrentProcesses
osCurrentProcesses.description: The current number of entries in the process table.

osSwapSpaceUsed.name: osSwapSpaceUsed
osSwapSpaceUsed.description: The amount of swap space in use in 512 byte blocks.

osFreeMemoryAvailable.name: osFreeMemoryAvailable
osFreeMemoryAvailable.description: The amount of executable space, in kilobytes, currently available.

osUserUsagePct.name: osUserUsagePct
osUserUsagePct.description: The percentage of time the CPU spent running processes that run in user space over the last five minutes.

osSysUsagePct.name: osSysUsagePct
osSysUsagePct.description: The percentage of time the CPU spent running processes that run in system mode over the last five minutes.

osWIOUsagePct.name: osWIOUsagePct
osWIOUsagePct.description: The percentage of time that the CPU was idle, but at least one process was waiting for an I/O operation to complete, over the last five minutes.

osIdleUsagePct.name: osIdleUsagePct
osIdleUsagePct.description: The percentage of time that the CPU was idle over the last five minutes.

osRunOccPct.name: osRunOccPct
osRunOccPct.description: The percentage of time that processes occupied the run queue over the last five minutes.

osSwapOccPct.name: osSwapOccPct
osSwapOccPct.description: The percentage of time that processes occupied the swap queue over the last five minutes.

osBuffRdRate.name: osBuffRdRate
osBuffRdRate.description: The average number of times per second that data was read from disk into UNIX system buffers over the last five minutes.

osRdCachePct.name: osRdCachePct
osRdCachePct.description: The percentage of read requests for UNIX system buffers that the kernel was able to service using existing UNIX system buffers, without reading new data from disk over the last five minutes.

osBuffWrRate.name: osBuffWrRate
osBuffWrRate.description: The average number of times per second that data was written from UNIX system buffers to disk over the last five minutes.

osWrCachePct.name: osWrCachePct
osWrCachePct.description: The percentage of write requests for UNIX system buffers that the kernel was able to service using existing UNIX system buffers, without writing new data to disk over the last five minutes.

osBswpInRate.name: osBswpInRate
osBswpInRate.description: The average number of 4 KB pages that were swapped or paged from disk to main memory per second over the last five minutes.

osBswpOutRate.name: osBswpOutRate
osBswpOutRate.description: The average number of 4 KB pages that were swapped or paged from main memory to disk per second over the last five minutes.

osVfltRate.name: osVfltRate
osVfltRate.description: The average number of validity faults per second over the last five minutes.

osSwitchRate.name: osSwitchRate
osSwitchRate.description: The average number of process switches per second over the last five minutes.

osSysCallRate.name: osSysCallRate
osSysCallRate.description: The average number of UNIX system calls that processes issued per second over the last five minutes.

nmLoadAvg15HighThres.name: nmLoadAvg15HighThres
nmLoadAvg15HighThres.description: A High threshold value for the 15-minute average of server load (ssLoadAvg15). If the value of ssLoadAvg15 goes above this, a VINES alert and a nmLoadAvgHigh Trap are generated.

nmSockInUseHighThres.name: nmSockInUseHighThres
nmSockInUseHighThres.description: A High threshold value for the percentage of maximum configured sockets currently in use (commSocksInUse). If the value of commSocksInUse goes above this, a VINES alert and a nmSockInUseHigh Trap are generated.

nmDiskUseHighThres.name: nmDiskUseHighThres
nmDiskUseHighThres.description: A High threshold value for the percentage of disk space in use on any given disk (dskUsedPct). If the value of dskUsedPct goes above this, a VINES alert and a nmDiskFull Trap are generated.

nmSwapAvgHighThres.name: nmSwapAvgHighThres
nmSwapAvgHighThres.description: A High threshold value for the 1-minute average of process swapping (ssSwapAvg). If the value of ssSwapAvg goes above this, a VINES alert and a nmSwapAvgHigh Trap are generated.

nmDropsHighThres.name: nmDropsHighThres
nmDropsHighThres.description: A High threshold value for the no. of messages dropped due to lack of comm buffer space (ssDrops). If the value of ssDrops goes above this, a VINES alert and a nmDropsHigh Trap are generated.

nmSwapSpaceLowThres.name: nmSwapSpaceLowThres
nmSwapSpaceLowThres.description: A Low threshold value for the amount of swap space available (osSwapSpaceAvailable). If the value of osSwapSpaceAvailable drops below this, a VINES alert and a nmFreeSwapLow Trap are generated.

nmFreeMemLowThres.name: nmFreeMemLowThres
nmFreeMemLowThres.description: A Low threshold value for the amount of memory free (osFreeMemoryAvailable). If the value of osFreeMemoryAvailable drops below this, a VINES alert and a nmFreeMemLow Trap are generated.

nmCommBuffHighThres.name: nmCommBuffHighThres
nmCommBuffHighThres.description: A High threshold value for the percentage of total comms buffer space currently in use (commBufUsage). If the value of commBufUsage goes above this, a VINES alert and a nmCommBuffHigh Trap are generated.

nmAllocFailHighThres.name: nmAllocFailHighThres
nmAllocFailHighThres.description: A High threshold value for the total of comm. buffers that could not be allocated since the last reboot (commAllocsFailed). If the value of commAllocsFailed goes above this, a VINES alert and a nmAllocFailHigh Trap are generated.

nmCacheHitsLowThres.name: nmCacheHitsLowThres
nmCacheHitsLowThres.description: A Low threshold value for the percentage of cache buffer requests that the system was able to service using existing cache buffers (fsPctCacheHits). If the value of fsPctCacheHits falls below this, a VINES alert and a nmCacheHitsLow Trap are generated.

nmDiskBusyHighThres.name: nmDiskBusyHighThres
nmDiskBusyHighThres.description: A High threshold value for the 5-minute average of the percentage of time a disk was in use transferring data (dskPctBusy). If the value of dskPctBusy rises above this, a VINES alert and a nmDiskBusy Trap are generated.

nmMsgAvgHighThres.name: nmMsgAvgHighThres
nmMsgAvgHighThres.description: A High threshold value for the 1-minute average of network messages sent/received per second (ssMsgAvg1). If the value of ssMsgAvg1 goes above this, a VINES alert and a nmMsgAvgHigh Trap are generated.

nmInodeUseHighThres.name: nmInodeUseHighThres
nmInodeUseHighThres.description: A High threshold value for the number of inode table entries currently in the inode table (osCurrentInodes). If the value of osCurrentInodes rises above this, a VINES alert and a nmInodesHigh Trap are generated.

tpAlertTime.name: tpAlertTime
tpAlertTime.description: The system time when alert was issued to the Alert Management Service, as specified in UNIX time() format.

tpSvcName.description: The StreetTalk Service name which issued the trap.

tpSvrName.name: tpSvrName
tpSvrName.description: The name of the Server on which the trap was issued.

tpJobId.name: tpJobId
tpJobId.description: The Job Identifier for a particular job in the Print Service.

tpPaperFormat.name: tpPaperFormat

tpJobTotal.name: tpJobTotal
tpJobTotal.description: The current number of jobs in the print queue.

tpConnId.name: tpConnId
tpConnId.description: A PostScript print service connection ID.

tpMailSender.name: tpMailSender
tpMailSender.description: The StreetTalk user name of a mail sender.

tpPortId.name: tpPortId
tpPortId.description: The Port ID being reported by VINES Security is the scene of a possible security breach.

tpRtnName.name: tpRtnName
tpRtnName.description: The name of the executing routine when the STDA service encountered a fatal error.

tp162errThresHigh.name: tp162errThresHigh
tp162errThresHigh.description: The High Threshold for 162 errors in ST.

tp162errTotal.name: tp162errTotal
tp162errTotal.description: The current total of 162 errors in ST.

tpNumGrps.name: tpNumGrps
tpNumGrps.description: The number of groups being maintained by StreetTalk on a given server (as a percentage of the maximum allowed no.

tpGrpLimit.name: tpGrpLimit
tpGrpLimit.description: The maximum number of groups allowed on a server.

tpDiskSpaceLeft.name: tpDiskSpaceLeft
tpDiskSpaceLeft.description: The amount of disk space left (KB) available to the Mail Service.

tpMailMessageId.name: tpMailMessageId
tpMailMessageId.description: The internal message ID of an item in the mail service.

tpSockOvFlowNum.name: tpSockOvFlowNum
tpSockOvFlowNum.description: The number of packets dropped due to a socket overflow.

tpDiskNName.name: tpDiskNName
tpDiskNName.description: The name of a disk unit.

tpSlotNum.name: tpSlotNum
tpSlotNum.description: The Slot Number of a particular interface card.

tpLineNum.name: tpLineNum
tpLineNum.description: The Line Number on the interface board.

tpLnkDropsThres.name: tpLnkDropsThres
tpLnkDropsThres.description: The threshold value for link-level drops - when exceeded an alert is issued.

tpLnkReXtThres.name: tpLnkReXtThres
tpLnkReXtThres.description: The threshold value for link-level re-transmits - when exceeded an alert is isssued.

amsRegTable.name: amsRegTable
amsRegTable.description: The Table containing entries for each seperate registration with AMS to receive alerts.

amsRegIndex.name: amsRegIndex
amsRegIndex.description: The index value into the amsRegTable used by SNMP.

amsRegIdInstance.name: amsRegIdInstance
amsRegIdInstance.description: The alert instance string that the registered party is interested in.

amsRegIdClass.name: amsRegIdClass
amsRegIdClass.description: The application class that the registered party is interested in receiving alerts from.

amsRegIdTid.name: amsRegIdTid
amsRegIdTid.description: The alert template identifier that the registered party is interested in.

amsRegPort.name: amsRegPort
amsRegPort.description: The Port to which the alerts are to be sent. This will be NULL if amsRegAction is something other than a notification sent to an IPC Port.

amsRegWhoAdded.name: amsRegWhoAdded
amsRegWhoAdded.description: The StreetTalk name of the user who added this particular entry to the table.

amsRegAlertee.name: amsRegAlertee
amsRegAlertee.description: The StreetTalk name of the user to whom the alerts are to be sent. This will be NULL if the amsRegAction for this entry is 'sendipcport'.

amsRegAction.name: amsRegAction
amsRegAction.description: The action to perform with alerts that match for this entry. The available options are : sendipcport - Pass the alert to the specific registered IPC port, as specified in 'amsRegPort'. bleepstname - Send a 25th-line message containing the alert to the user 'amsRegAlertee'.

amsAlertLogTable.name: amsAlertLogTable
amsAlertLogTable.description: The Table containing entries for each each record written into each of the AMS alert log files.

amsLogFileIndex.name: amsLogFileIndex
amsLogFileIndex.description: The index value into the amsRegTable used to distinguish between the alert log files kept by AMS. Options are: previous - The previous day's log. current - Today's log file. The log files are switched at 12:00am each night, when 'today' becomes 'yesterday' and 'yesterday' is emptied and becomes 'today'.

amsLogRecIndex.name: amsLogRecIndex
amsLogRecIndex.description: The index value into the amsAlertLogTable used to uniquely identify each record in a given alert log.

amsLogIdInstance.name: amsLogIdInstance
amsLogIdInstance.description: The alert instance string of the AlertID in the alert record.

amsLogIdClass.name: amsLogIdClass
amsLogIdClass.description: The application class of the AlertID in the alert record.

amsLogIdTid.name: amsLogIdTid
amsLogIdTid.description: The template identifier of the AlertID in the alert record.

amsLogAlertTime.name: amsLogAlertTime
amsLogAlertTime.description: The time at which the alert was originally issued.

amsLogAlertString.name: amsLogAlertString
amsLogAlertString.description: The textual string description of the alert including all data values.

mlMBTableIndex.name: mlMBTableIndex
mlMBTableIndex.description: The index value into the mlMailBoxTable used by SNMP.

mlMBTableMBOwner.name: mlMBTableMBOwner
mlMBTableMBOwner.description: The StreetTalk name of the user to whom this mailbox relates.

mlMBTableUnreadMsgs.name: mlMBTableUnreadMsgs
mlMBTableUnreadMsgs.description: The number of unread messages in this mailbox.

mlMBTableTotalMsgs.name: mlMBTableTotalMsgs
mlMBTableTotalMsgs.description: The total number of messages in this mailbox.

vlogsTable.description: The Table containing entries for each log.

vlogsFileIndex.name: vlogsFileIndex
vlogsFileIndex.description: The index value into the vlogsTable.

vlogsDescr.name: vlogsDescr
vlogsDescr.description: The record entry for the log.

nmLoadAvgHigh.name: nmLoadAvgHigh
nmLoadAvgHigh.description: The 15 minute load average on the specified server has exceeded the specified threshold value.

nmSwapAvgHigh.name: nmSwapAvgHigh
nmSwapAvgHigh.description: The 15 minute swap average on the specified server has exceeded the specified threshold value.

nmDropsHigh.name: nmDropsHigh
nmDropsHigh.description: The 15 minute average of dropped messages (due to lack of comms buffers) on the specified server has exceeded the specified threshold value.

nmFreeSwapLow.name: nmFreeSwapLow
nmFreeSwapLow.description: The Free Swap space on the specified server fell below the specified threshold value.

nmFreeMemLow.name: nmFreeMemLow
nmFreeMemLow.description: The Free Process memory space on the specified server fell below the specified threshold value.

nmCommBuffHigh.name: nmCommBuffHigh
nmCommBuffHigh.description: The communications buffer usage on the specified server exceeded the specified threshold value.

nmSockInUseHigh.name: nmSockInUseHigh
nmSockInUseHigh.description: The sockets in use on the specified server exceeded the specified threshold value.

nmSockOvflow.name: nmSockOvflow
nmSockOvflow.description: Socket overflow for the specified service. The number of packets dropped is also provided.

nmMsgAvgHigh.name: nmMsgAvgHigh
nmMsgAvgHigh.description: The 15 minute average of message activity on the specified server has exceeded the specified threshold value.

nmAllocFail_High.name: nmAllocFail_High
nmAllocFail_High.description: The number of failed communication buffer allocations on the specified server exceeded the specified threshold value.

nmCacheHits_Low.name: nmCacheHits_Low
